data.meta_description:
850 likes, 11 comments - azcentral on February 17, 2024: "Just past the 22nd anniversary of Country Music Hall of Famer Waylon Jennings' death. With over 60 albums throughout his career and 16 No. 1 country singles, the memory of the songwriter continues to be fondly cherished by fans and honored in country culture.

Jennings died at the age of 64 on Feb. 13, 2002, at his home in Chandler. Following his death, the country music legend was buried in a Mesa cemetery.
